Ireland's 2020 Payment towards Programme Quality, Support and Development: Miscellaneous activities - 2020)
Program Quality and Management Costs are required to support the implementation of programme activities such as research, planning, and administration costs.

The Ireland Fellows Programme enables early to mid-career professionals from eligible countries to undertake a fully funded one-year master’s level programme at a higher education institution in Ireland in a field of study aligned with Ireland’s policy priorities. The aims of the Programme are to nurture future leaders; to develop in-country capacity to achieve national SDG goals; and to build positive relationships with Ireland.
